\f1\b\fs125\fsmilli62568 \cf0 VII. Baptism and the Lord\'92s Supper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa351\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs42\fsmilli21120 \cf0 Christian baptism is the immersion of a believer in water in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit. It is an act of obedience symbolizing the believer\'92s faith in a crucified, buried, and risen Saviour, the believer\'92s death to sin, the burial of the old life, and the resurrection to walk in newness of life in Christ Jesus. It is a testimony to his faith in the final resurrection of the dead. Being a church ordinance, it is prerequisite to the privileges of church membership and to the Lord\'92s Supper.\
The Lord\'92s Supper is a symbolic act of obedience whereby members of the church, through partaking of the bread and the fruit of the vine, memorialize the death of the Redeemer and anticipate His second coming.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa351\partightenfactor0
