\f1\b\fs125\fsmilli62568 \cf0 VIII. The Lord\'92s Day\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa351\partightenfactor0

\f3\b0\fs42\fsmilli21120 \cf0 The first day of the week is the Lord\'92s Day. It is a Christian institution for regular observance. It commemorates the resurrection of Christ from the dead and should include exercises of worship and spiritual devotion, both public and private. Activities on the Lord\'92s Day should be commensurate with the Christian\'92s conscience under the Lordship of Jesus Christ.\
